  @startuml ILM — JWT Auth Flow
  !theme plain
  skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
  skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
  skinparam defaultFontSize 11
  skinparam shadowing false
  skinparam RoundCorner 6
  skinparam SequenceLifeLineBorderColor #94A3B8
  skinparam SequenceGroupBorderColor #CBD5E1
  skinparam SequenceGroupBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  skinparam SequenceDividerBackgroundColor #EFF6FF
  skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  skinparam ParticipantBorderColor #94A3B8
  skinparam DatabaseBackgroundColor #FFF7ED
  skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFFBEB
  skinparam NoteBorderColor #CBD5E1
  skinparam ArrowColor #475569

  title JWT Authentication & Authorization Flow

  actor User as U
  participant "React Frontend" as FE #F0F9FF
  participant "Supabase Auth" as AUTH #FEF3C7
  participant "NestJS API" as API #F0FDF4
  database "PostgreSQL" as DB #FFF7ED

  == LOGIN (unchanged — Supabase OTP) ==

  U -> FE : Enter email
  FE -> AUTH : check_usuario_email_exists(email)
  AUTH -> DB : user exists + ativo + municipio ativo?
  DB --> AUTH : ok
  AUTH --> U : OTP email

  U -> FE : Enter OTP code
  FE -> AUTH : verifyOtp(email, code)
  AUTH --> FE : JWT signed with JWT_SECRET

  note over AUTH
    **JWT payload:**
    { sub: "a1b2c3d4-...",
      email: "juliana@escola.com",
      role: "authenticated" }
    No perfil, no municipio — just identity
  end note

  FE -> FE : Store in localStorage

  == MIGRATED REQUEST (escola via NestJS) ==

  U -> FE : Open /admin/escolas
  FE -> API : **GET /api/escolas**\nBearer {jwt}
  activate API

  group #F8FAFC ① JWT Validation — JwtStrategy
      API -> API : Verify signature (HS256)\nwith SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET\n//no HTTP call to Supabase//
      API -> API : Check exp not expired
      API -> API : Extract sub = "a1b2c3d4-..."
  end

  group #F8FAFC ② User Resolution — validate()
      API -> DB : SELECT usuario + perfil\nWHERE auth_user_id = sub
      DB --> API : { perfil: "diretor",\nmunicipio_id: "xyz",\nescola_ids: ["abc"] }
      API -> API : Attach to req.user
  end

  note right of API
    **Replaces Supabase SQL helpers:**
    current_perfil() → req.user.perfil
    current_municipio_id() → req.user.municipio_id
    can_diretor_see_*() → CASL ability
  end note

  group #F8FAFC ③ Authorization — CASL
      API -> API : Build ability for "diretor":\ncan('read', 'escola', { id: {$in: escola_ids} })\ncan('update', 'escola', { id: {$in: escola_ids} })
      API -> API : CaslGuard: can('read', 'Escola')? → ok
  end

  group #F8FAFC ④ Query — Prisma
      API -> DB : escola.findMany()\nscoped by accessibleBy(ability)
      DB --> API : [{ nome: "Escola Municipal..." }]
  end

  API --> FE : 200 { data: [...], total: 1 }
  deactivate API
  FE --> U : Render table

  == NON-MIGRATED REQUEST (turma — still direct) ==

  FE -> DB : supabase.from('turma')...\n//same JWT, RLS still active//
  DB --> FE : { data: [...] }

  note over FE, AUTH
    Token refresh is automatic (Supabase client).
    NestJS is stateless — no session, no sync needed.
  end note

  @enduml